I explored the repository from disk first, focusing on the implemented surfaces in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`, `pkg/workloadmanager`, `client-go`, and the deployment assets under `manifests`, `docker`, `Makefile`, and `test/e2e`. The CRD, generated client, Helm, Docker, and build assets already matched the current spec text closely, so the only code gaps I found were in the workload-manager create path.

I updated `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` to make create handling stricter and more spec-aligned: a client-supplied `kind` is now validated when present, including blank/whitespace values; Kubernetes API-style service errors can now surface as `404` or `401` instead of always collapsing to `500`; and a nil create response is treated as an internal error instead of returning a malformed `200`. I added focused coverage in `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go` for whitespace `kind`, not-found/unauthorized error mapping, and nil-response handling.

I could not run `go test ./...` to finish runtime verification because every shell command in this session was rejected by the environment, so execution-based verification is still pending. The next step, once command execution is available, is to run `go test ./...` from the repo root.
